The broad emission band upon the excitation of 460 nm is exactly deconvoluted into two Gaussian spectral profiles with two peaks at 13900 cm−1 (719 nm) and 12750 cm−1 (784 nm), suggesting that Eu2+ substitute two different cations in K3LuSi2O7 (Fig. 2c). Figure 2d shows the PL decay curves of K3LuSi2O7:0.01Eu2+ measured at low temperature (80 K) and at room temperature (300 K) under 450 nm pulse laser diode excitation. The decay curves were comparatively fitted by mono- (n = 1), bi- (n = 2) and triple- (n = 3) exponential functions:121\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
